    "module": "module TopModule (\n    input [3:0] x,\n    output f\n);\n\n    // Using combinational logic to implement the function from Karnaugh map\n    always @(*) begin\n        // The Karnaugh map analysis gives us:\n        // f = x[3]'x[2]'x[1]'x[0] + x[3]'x[2]'x[1]x[0] + x[3]x[2]'x[1]'x[0] + x[3]x[2]'x[1]x[0] + x[3]x[2]x[1]'x[0] + x[3]x[2]x[1]x[0]\n        // Simplifying using K-map groups:\n        // Group 1: x[3]'x[2]'x[0] + x[3]x[2]'x[0] = x[2]'x[0]\n        // Group 2: x[3]x[2]x[1]'x[0] + x[3]x[2]x[1]x[0] = x[3]x[2]x[0]\n        // Group 3: x[3]'x[2]'x[1]'x[0] + x[3]x[2]'x[1]'x[0] = x[2]'x[1]'x[0]\n        // Group 4: x[3]x[2]'x[1]x[0] + x[3]x[2]x[1]x[0] = x[3]x[0]\n        \n        // Further simplification:\n        // f = x[2]'x[0] + x[3]x[2]x[0] + x[2]'x[1]'x[0] + x[3]x[0]\n        // This can be factored further: f = x[0] (x[2]' + x[3]x[2] + x[2]'x[1]' + x[3])\n        \n        // Let's manually construct it based on Karnaugh map values:\n        f = (x[3] & ~x[2] & ~x[1] & ~x[0]) |\n            (~x[3] & ~x[2] & x[1] & x[0]) |\n            (x[3] & ~x[2] & ~x[1] & x[0]) |\n            (x[3] & ~x[2] & x[1] & x[0]) |\n            (x[3] & x[2] & ~x[1] & x[0]) |\n            (x[3] & x[2] & x[1] & x[0]);\n    end\n\nendmodule"
